cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): This paper discusses tracking and data management, which are key components of computer vision. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): Mobile AR has a strong focus on user interaction and experience, which falls under the domain of HCI. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): AR involves rendering virtual objects in the real world, which is a graphics-related task. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): AR involves combining multiple types of media (real and virtual), which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality): This paper is specifically about Mobile Augmented Reality, so it is highly likely to belong to the AR sub-category.
